Nad's Natural Hair Removal Gel Wax Kit.

Sue Ismiel & Daughters

About Us: Before Nad’s was created back in 1992, no one ever talked about unwanted hair. That first pot of Nad’s Natural Hair Removal Gel changed everything. Today, Nad’s - led by founder Sue Ismiel and her daughters - is renowned as the hair removal innovator, with products tailored, tested and proven to solve the real problem of unwanted hair for women and men around the world.

Nad's Natural Hair Removal Gel Wax Kit

Complete wax kit for the best hair removal results at home

Nad's has put everything you need for the best hair removal results at home in a convenient wax kit! Nad's Natural Hair Removal Gel is the original no-heat formula that warms with body heat as it’s smoothed onto the skin and waxed away - along with your unwanted hair - to leave the skin salon smooth for up to four weeks. Best of all, if you make a mistake with application, the formula simply rinses off with water.

  • Gentle gel wax suitable for all skin types
  • Ideal for body, legs, arms, bikini, underarms, and face
  • Smooth results of up to 8 weeks
  • No heat formula - The wax melts with your body heat
  • Contains natural ingredients - So natural you can eat it
  • Wax with confidence - Wax easily washes away with water
  • Kit contains: 1 Nad’s Natural Hair Removal Gel 170g (6oz), 4 Nad’s Pre Wax Cleansing Wipes, 6 Spatulas, 100% Premium Cotton Strips, 1 Moisture + Soothing Body Balm 15g (0.53oz), instruction leaflet

How to use Nad's Hair Removal Gel

View larger

View larger

View larger

View larger

Prep the area to be treated

Start by throughly cleansing the area with a Nad's Pre-Wax Cleansing Wipe. Completely dry the area.

Hair should be between 3 to 5 mm long for best results.

Apply the gel wax

Coat the spatula with a good portion of gel wax and slowly apply a thin and even layer in the direction of hair growth.

Tip: If the environment is cold or the gel is too thick, heat in the microwave for 5 - 10 seconds.

Place the cotton strip

Immediately place a cotton strip over the gel and with the palm of your hand firmly smooth over the strip 3 to 4 times in the direction of hair growth.

Remove the strip

Holding the skin taut, quickly remove the strip in one swift motion in the opposite direction of hair growth. Use warm water to remove any gel wax residue and finish by using Nad's Moisture + Soothing Balm on the treated area.

All done. Enjoy up to 8 weeks of silky smooth skin.

How does Amazon calculate star ratings?

K. Stoyanov
5.0 out of 5 stars Works great for course hair. Great for Men.
Reviewed in the United States on August 26, 2017
Size: 6 OunceVerified Purchase
Works great for men. Even on short hairs, or thick hairs, or deep stubborn hairs. Ignore the people leaving 1-3 star reviews. They're not using it correctly.

1) You NEED to wash the area with good soap without conditioner and moisturizers so you can get rid of all body oils on the skin and hair otherwise the wax/gel won't grab onto the hairs, and the oil from your skin will just cover the top most layer of wax/gel.

2) Put the gel on the cloth first. Not on your skin.

3) The gel gets gooey'er with bodyheat. So as soon as you put the gel on the cloth and put it on your skin pat it down firmly quickly so it grabs the hairs and immediately pull in the opposite direction. You should not be letting the gel touch your skin for more than 2 seconds. Act fast and quit being a wimp.

4) Let the gel cool off a bit in between waxing for 5 seconds. wave it in the air then wax with it again. Your body temp is in the 90s so it's melting it and making it gooey.

Wash the cloths afterwords with hot water and the gel and hair in it will wash right off.

Soak them in hot water and work the gel/wax off the strips and let them fully dry.

This is my first time using this product and I am in love! It hurts a lot less than those hard waxes or other methods I've used. Kelley
2.0 out of 5 stars Great way to get "me time" not great way to remove body hair - Inefficient
Reviewed in the United States on March 1, 2017
Size: 6 OunceVerified Purchase
If you are expecting hair removal like that shown on the Nad's advertisements you will be disappointed. I will share my novice, though determined, Nad's experience and how I was able to get the best results.

It is possible that my hair is thicker than most people's, but I was not able to remove ALL hair from any place on my body despite going over each area more than once. Even if an area looked smooth, it didn't feel smooth. My legs and bikini area started bleeding before I was able to remove both coarse and fine hairs. This one container wouldn't have covered legs and bikini and underarm area in one use even if I had had enough cotton strips and three hours to spend on waxing.

I had the best results when I:
1) cut the provided strips in half. Working in smaller sections seemed to get more hair off on the first pass
2) heated the gel in the microwave for 15 (full container) or 10 (half-full or less) seconds, stirred and then placed in a shallow hot water bath when not spreading it.
3) worked on a couple sections at a time by spreading the gel on a section of skin, put on the cotton strip and waiting a minute before pulling it off parallel to the skin.

I won't be buying Nad's again. I tried different part of the body several times until I had used up the whole container. I let my hair grown out in between trials. Overall, I say it removed about 20-80% of the hair, with effectiveness going down with each trial even though I stored it according to package instructions. Using Nad's is a great excuse if you need some time alone, not a great way to get smooth legs.
